"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/896334","Department of Health and Social Care","false","2018-05-14","<p>NHS England has advised that it does not publish individual responses to consultations that the respondent has not themselves put into the public domain.</p><p> </p><p>Further information about the consultation decision can be found here:</p><p> </p><p><a href="https://assets.publishing.service.gov.uk/government/uploads/system/uploads/attachment_data/file/510665/PSSAG_report_2015.pdf" target="_blank">https://assets.publishing.service.gov.uk/government/uploads/system/uploads/attachment_data/file/510665/PSSAG_report_2015.pdf</a></p>","Winchester","Steve Brine",,"2018-05-14T11:26:29.15Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/896334/answer","Biography information for Steve Brine","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/896334/answer",,,,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/896334/answer",,,,,"17","Health and Social Care","Health and Social Care","2018-05-02","Kidney Diseases: Medical Treatments","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Health and Social Care, which (a) organisations and (b) individuals were consulted by NHS England when it was developing its proposal to move commissioning of dialysis to clinical commissioning groups; and if he will publish the contents of the submissions which were received in response to that consultation.","false","Biography information for Jonathan Ashworth","Leicester South","Jonathan Ashworth","140728"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/896335","Department of Health and Social Care","false","2018-05-14","<p>The Department’s policy is that grant funding should not be provided to third parties to lobby the Department. Since May 2017 the grant agreements with third parties specifically state in the terms and conditions that this is not eligible.</p>","Gosport","Caroline Dinenage",,"2018-05-14T11:18:44.927Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/896335/answer","Biography information for Caroline Dinenage","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/896335/answer",,,,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/896335/answer",,,,,"17","Health and Social Care","Health and Social Care","2018-05-02","Department of Health and Social Care: Lobbying","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Health and Social Care, what his policy is on use of grant funding provided by his Department to third parties to lobby his Department.","false","Biography information for Jonathan Ashworth","Leicester South","Jonathan Ashworth","140729"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/896336","Department of Health and Social Care","false","2018-05-14","<p>Data on the number of patients who died due to a hospital acquired infection are not available in the format requested.</p><p> </p><p>Estimated 30-day all-cause deaths among patients following bacteraemia (bloodstream infection) due to meticillin-resistant <em>Staphylococcus aureus</em>, meticillin-susceptible <em>Staphylococcus aureus</em> and <em>Escherichia coli</em> bacteraemia and <em>Clostridium difficile</em> infection for the years 2013–17 are available to view here:</p><p> </p><p><a href="https://www.gov.uk/government/statistics/mrsa-mssa-and-e-coli-bacteraemia-and-c-difficile-infection-30-day-all-cause-fatality" target="_blank">https://www.gov.uk/government/statistics/mrsa-mssa-and-e-coli-bacteraemia-and-c-difficile-infection-30-day-all-cause-fatality</a></p>","Gosport","Caroline Dinenage",,"2018-05-14T11:21:19.843Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/896336/answer","Biography information for Caroline Dinenage","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/896336/answer",,,,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/896336/answer",,,,,"17","Health and Social Care","Health and Social Care","2018-05-02","Hospitals: Infectious Diseases","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Health and Social Care, how many patients died due to a hospital acquired infection in primary care trusts in (a) 2017, (b) 2016, (c) 2015, (d) 2014 and (e) 2013.","false","Biography information for Jonathan Ashworth","Leicester South","Jonathan Ashworth","140730"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/896337","Department of Health and Social Care","false","2018-05-14","<p>The number of defibrillators provided in each building the Department manages is shown in the following table.</p><p> </p><table><tbody><tr><td><p>Building</p></td><td><p>Number of defibrillators</p></td></tr><tr><td><p>39 Victoria Street (London)</p></td><td><p>10</p></td></tr><tr><td><p>Skipton House (London)</p></td><td><p>6</p></td></tr><tr><td><p>Wellington House (London)</p></td><td><p>9</p></td></tr><tr><td><p>Blenheim House (Leeds)</p></td><td><p>3</p></td></tr><tr><td><p>Premier House (Reading)</p></td><td><p>4</p></td></tr></tbody></table>","Gosport","Caroline Dinenage",,"2018-05-14T11:14:14.62Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/896337/answer","Biography information for Caroline Dinenage","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/896337/answer",,,,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/896337/answer",,,,,"17","Health and Social Care","Health and Social Care","2018-05-02","Department of Health and Social Care: Defibrillators","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Health and Social Care, how many defibrillators are provided in each building his Department manages.","false","Biography information for Jonathan Ashworth","Leicester South","Jonathan Ashworth","140731"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/896338","Department of Health and Social Care","false","2018-05-14","<p>Fire safety checks of National Health Service facilities, including hospitals, are regularly undertaken in line with legislation and guidance. This data is not collected centrally.</p><p> </p><p>Fire safety guidance is available in the following Health Technical Memorandum (HTM) 05 publication provided to NHS organisations: “HTM 05-02: Firecode Guidance in support of functional provisions (Fire safety in the design of healthcare premises)” 2015 edition. All Firecode guidance will be reviewed following the recommendations of the Dame Judith Hackitt’s final report on Building Regulations and Fire Safety, when it is published.</p>","North East Cambridgeshire","Stephen Barclay",,"2018-05-14T16:27:44.12Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/896338/answer","Biography information for Stephen Barclay","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/896338/answer",,,,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/896338/answer",,,,,"17","Health and Social Care","Health and Social Care","2018-05-02","NHS: Fire Prevention","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Health and Social Care, what data the Government collects centrally on whether (a) standard fire safety checks around building structures, (b) escape routes, (c) fire alarms and (d) sprinklers are up to date across all NHS sites.","false","Biography information for Jonathan Ashworth","Leicester South","Jonathan Ashworth","140732"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/896339","Department of Health and Social Care","false","2018-05-10","<p>NHS Blood and Transplant (NHSBT) is the organ donor organisation for the United Kingdom and is responsible for promoting organ donation, maintaining the national transplant waiting list and the matching and offering of donated organs.</p><p> </p><p>The policies for allocating lungs are developed in collaboration with the Cardiothoracic Advisory Group (comprised of cardiothoracic surgeons (lung and heart), commissioners and NHSBT) to ensure that the processes are clear, transparent and clinically effective. New systems were introduced in May 2017, to help ensure that the available lungs are offered to the most clinically urgent patients on the transplant waiting list.</p><p> </p><p>Since this policy has been introduced, the following improvements have been observed:</p><p>- An increase in the number of patients receiving a transplant within one month of listing, with those in the clinically urgent groups receiving a transplant within two weeks on average; and</p><p>- A 15% increase in the number of lung transplants performed nationally.</p><p> </p><p>The policies and processes relating to lung donation and allocation are monitored closely by NHSBT and further amendments will be made to the allocation policy if necessary.</p>","Thurrock","Jackie Doyle-Price",,"2018-05-10T14:30:07.547Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/896339/answer","Biography information for Jackie Doyle-Price","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/896339/answer",,,,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/896339/answer",,,,,"17","Health and Social Care","Health and Social Care","2018-05-02","Lung Diseases: Transplant Surgery","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Health and Social Care, what plans he has to improve the matching of donated lungs with people waiting for lung transplants.","false","Biography information for Jonathan Ashworth","Leicester South","Jonathan Ashworth","140733"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/896340","Department for Digital, Culture, Media and Sport","false","2018-05-14","<p>Aviation heritage plays a valuable role in our tourism economy. Events such as the Farnborough Airshow attract hundreds of thousands of tourists, and support the local economy, as well as being good for our aerospace and defence industry. My Department sponsors the Imperial War Museum at Duxford, which is visited by almost 400,000 visitors every year, and houses everything from Spitfires to Concorde.</p><p> </p><p>The Heritage Lottery Fund is also open to applications which celebrate our rich aviation history. Recent recipients include Brooklands Museum in Weybridge, an historic site for aviation manufacturing and a successful tourist attraction given £4.7million, and the Stow Maries First World War Aerodrome in Essex, recently granted £4.3million to turn it into a major visitor attraction.</p>","Northampton North","Michael Ellis",,"2018-05-14T12:29:47.463Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/896340/answer","Biography information for Michael Ellis","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/896340/answer",,,,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/896340/answer",,,,,"10","Digital, Culture, Media and Sport","Digital, Culture, Media and Sport","2018-05-02","Cultural Heritage: Aircraft","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Digital, Culture, Media and Sport, what assessment he has made of the level of the contribution of the heritage aviation sector to the UK economy.","false","Biography information for Leo Docherty","Aldershot","Leo Docherty","140839"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/896341","Department for Digital, Culture, Media and Sport","false","2018-05-14","<p>DCMS is a sponsor of VisitBritain and VisitEngland - who provide support for all types of hospitality and tourism stakeholders.</p><p> </p><p>VisitBritain and VisitEngland make available a comprehensive library of guidance for tourism businesses - ranging from step by step marketing guides to advice on how to implement tourism related regulation.</p><p> </p><p>In addition, VisitEngland supports tourism businesses through the £40 million Discover England Fund. There are no airshows included in the current projects.</p>","Northampton North","Michael Ellis",,"2018-05-14T12:27:34.78Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/896341/answer","Biography information for Michael Ellis","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/896341/answer",,,,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/896341/answer",,,,,"10","Digital, Culture, Media and Sport","Digital, Culture, Media and Sport","2018-05-02","Air Displays","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Digital, Culture, Media and Sport, what steps his Department is taking to support airshows throughout the UK.","false","Biography information for Leo Docherty","Aldershot","Leo Docherty","140840"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/896342","Ministry of Defence","false","2018-05-09","<p>The number of women recruited into the Army in each of the last three financial years can be found at the following link (Table 7 of the excel spreadsheet):</p><p>https://www.gov.uk/government/statistics/uk-armed-forces-biannual-diversity-statistics-2017</p>","Bournemouth East","Mr Tobias Ellwood",,"2018-05-09T15:54:47.587Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/896342/answer","Biography information for Mr Tobias Ellwood","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/896342/answer",,,,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/896342/answer",,,,,"11","Defence","Defence","2018-05-02","Army: Females","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Defence, how many women have been recruited to the Army in each of the last three years.","false","Biography information for Mr Gregory Campbell","East Londonderry","Mr Gregory Campbell","140643"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/896343","Department for Digital, Culture, Media and Sport","false","2018-05-14","<p>VisitBritain and VisitEngland are responsible for promoting the UK as a tourist destination, through a range of different initiatives and campaigns. London features in many of VisitBritain’s campaign, such as the current global marketing campaign ‘I Travel For’ to increase inbound tourism to Great Britain.</p><p> </p><p>VisitBritain also work with travel and tourism partners such as Sony Pictures and Studio Canal, to promote filming locations across London, and Barclays Premier League to convert football fans to visitors, promoting London stadia and their surrounding neighbourhoods. Additionally, VisitBritain work closely with London and Partners to ensure complementary marketing campaigns, including investing £500,000 in London &amp; Partners’ Autumn Season campaign. They are also supporting London &amp; Partners’ culture and dispersal messaging – helping attract visitors to London’s vibrant outer neighbourhoods and supporting the Mayor’s priority of delivering for all Londoners.</p>","Northampton North","Michael Ellis",,"2018-05-14T12:31:35.59Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/896343/answer","Biography information for Michael Ellis","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/896343/answer",,,,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/896343/answer",,,,,"10","Digital, Culture, Media and Sport","Digital, Culture, Media and Sport","2018-05-02","Tourism: Greater London","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Digital, Culture, Media and Sport, what steps his Department is taking to promote tourism in outer London.","false","Biography information for Sir David Evennett","Bexleyheath and Crayford","David Evennett","140608"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/896344","Department of Health and Social Care","false","2018-05-09","<p>The Department has no plans to legislate for integrated care systems.</p>","Gosport","Caroline Dinenage",,"2018-05-09T15:01:56.497Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/896344/answer","Biography information for Caroline Dinenage","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/896344/answer",,,,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/896344/answer",,,,,"17","Health and Social Care","Health and Social Care","2018-05-02","Integrated Care Systems","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Health and Social Care, what plans he has to bring forward legislative proposals for integrated care systems in the NHS.","false","Biography information for Mr Jim Cunningham","Coventry South","Mr Jim Cunningham","140568"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/896345","Home Office","false","2018-05-09","<p>The Home Office collects and publishes statistics on the number of stop and searches and subsequent arrests, conducted by each police force in England and Wales. The Home Office collects these data at Police Force Area level only and does not hold this information at constituency level.</p><p> </p><p>These data are published in the ‘Police Powers and Procedures, England and Wales’ statistical bulletins, and latest available data for the year ending March 2017 can be accessed here:</p><p><a href="https://www.gov.uk/government/statistics/police-powers-and-procedures-england-and-wales-year-ending-31-march-2017" target="_blank">https://www.gov.uk/government/statistics/police-powers-and-procedures-england-and-wales-year-ending-31-march-2017</a></p><p> </p><p>Data on stop and searches are broken down by the reason for the search or subsequent arrest and the ethnicity of the person being searched. Data from 2006/07 onwards can be found in the Open Data Table accompanying the Police Powers and Procedures bulletin:</p><p><a href="https://www.gov.uk/government/uploads/system/uploads/attachment_data/file/654473/stop-search-open-data-tables-ppp.ods" target="_blank">https://www.gov.uk/government/uploads/system/uploads/attachment_data/file/654473/stop-search-open-data-tables-ppp.ods</a></p>","Ruislip, Northwood and Pinner","Mr Nick Hurd","140610","2018-05-09T17:06:02.227Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/896345/answer","Biography information for Mr Nick Hurd","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/896345/answer",,,,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/896345/answer",,,,,"1","Home Office","Home Office","2018-05-02","Stop and Search: Greater London","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for the Home Department, how many people have been stopped and searched in (a) London, (b) the London Borough of Bexley and (c) Bexleyheath and Crayford constituency in each of the last five years.","false","Biography information for Sir David Evennett","Bexleyheath and Crayford","David Evennett","140609"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/896346","Ministry of Defence","false","2018-05-08","<p>I am pleased to be able to confirm that 296 (Stoke Newington) Squadron Air Training Corps will continue to operate from its existing premises, with a review period of 12 months.</p>","Bournemouth East","Mr Tobias Ellwood",,"2018-05-08T15:43:19.333Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/896346/answer","Biography information for Mr Tobias Ellwood","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/896346/answer",,,,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/896346/answer",,,,,"11","Defence","Defence","2018-05-02","Air Training Corps: Stoke Newington","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Defence, what steps he is taking to ensure that the 296 Stoke Newington Air Training Corps will be relocated following the closure of the site on the Albion Road.","false","Biography information for David Simpson","Upper Bann","David Simpson","140694"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/896347","Home Office","false","2018-05-09","<p>The Home Office collects and publishes statistics on the number of stop and searches and subsequent arrests, conducted by each police force in England and Wales. The Home Office collects these data at Police Force Area level only and does not hold this information at constituency level.</p><p> </p><p>These data are published in the ‘Police Powers and Procedures, England and Wales’ statistical bulletins, and latest available data for the year ending March 2017 can be accessed here:</p><p><a href="https://www.gov.uk/government/statistics/police-powers-and-procedures-england-and-wales-year-ending-31-march-2017" target="_blank">https://www.gov.uk/government/statistics/police-powers-and-procedures-england-and-wales-year-ending-31-march-2017</a></p><p> </p><p>Data on stop and searches are broken down by the reason for the search or subsequent arrest and the ethnicity of the person being searched. Data from 2006/07 onwards can be found in the Open Data Table accompanying the Police Powers and Procedures bulletin:</p><p><a href="https://www.gov.uk/government/uploads/system/uploads/attachment_data/file/654473/stop-search-open-data-tables-ppp.ods" target="_blank">https://www.gov.uk/government/uploads/system/uploads/attachment_data/file/654473/stop-search-open-data-tables-ppp.ods</a></p>","Ruislip, Northwood and Pinner","Mr Nick Hurd","140609","2018-05-09T17:06:02.29Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/896347/answer","Biography information for Mr Nick Hurd","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/896347/answer",,,,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/896347/answer",,,,,"1","Home Office","Home Office","2018-05-02","Stop and Search","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for the Home Department,  how many people were stopped and searched by the Police in each of the last five years; and how many of those people were subsequently arrested.","false","Biography information for Sir D