"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/896353","Foreign and Commonwealth Office","false","2018-05-14","<p><strong><em>​</em></strong>Tackling terrorism in South Asia is regularly discussed with partners, including our NATO Allies. During the NATO Foreign Ministers meeting in Brussels on 27 April, the Foreign Secretary discussed the issue of terrorist groups operating in both Pakistan and Afghanistan, the implications they have for regional security, and the ongoing efforts to tackle them.</p>","Cities of London and Westminster","Mark Field",,"2018-05-14T13:19:37.5Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/896353/answer","Biography information for Mark Field","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/896353/answer",,,,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/896353/answer",,,,,"16","Foreign and Commonwealth Office","Foreign and Commonwealth Office","2018-05-02","Pakistan: Terrorism","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Foreign and Commonwealth Affairs, what recent discussions he has had with NATO partners on tackling terrorism by groups based in Pakistan.","false","Biography information for Nigel Dodds","Belfast North","Nigel Dodds","140620"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/896354","Foreign and Commonwealth Office","false","2018-05-09","<p>We are keeping our Be on the Ball travel advice for the 2018 World Cup under regular review. Since the page was first published in June 2017, we have issued five updates to date, on 14 November, 1 December, 15 February, 21 March and 6 April. We encourage travelling fans to keep up to date with the campaign and our Travel Advice for Russia. We will continue to issue updates in the build-up and during the tournament.</p>","West Worcestershire","Harriett Baldwin",,"2018-05-09T14:59:25.657Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/896354/answer","Biography information for Harriett Baldwin","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/896354/answer",,,,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/896354/answer",,,,,"16","Foreign and Commonwealth Office","Foreign and Commonwealth Office","2018-05-02","Russia: Travel Information","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Foreign and Commonwealth Affairs, how many updates have been made to the Be on the Ball travel advice since June 2017; and on what dates those updates were published.","false","Biography information for Tom Watson","West Bromwich East","Tom Watson","140653"
